                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-673">
                        <quote source="#bib673-1">Theologian, biblical commentator, and bp. of Nisibis, for which position he was
            selected in 544 by Cath. Mar Aba, his former teacher.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="description">In hagiography: In hagiography: Paul of Nisibis was
          originally from <placeName>Prat Maysan</placeName>. He was a disciple of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/306">Mar Aba I</persName> who signed the synod of Joseph
          in 554. He was an intermediary between <persName>Khusro</persName> and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284">Justinian</persName> and <persName>Justin
            II</persName>. He debated also with <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/530">Henana
            of Adiabene</persName> over theology of the Church of the East.</note>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib673-5">male</sex>
